    pageItem P320_BLOG_POST (
        type: richTextEditor
        label {
            label: <strong>Blog Post</strong>
            alignment: left
        }
        settings {
            minHeight: 180
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 90
            region: @go-to-market-social
            slot: regionBody
            alignment: left
        }
        appearance {
            template: @optional-above
            templateOptions: #DEFAULT#
        }
        source {
            formRegion: @go-to-market-social
            column: BLOG_POST
            dataType: varchar2
            queryOnly: true
        }
        help {
            inlineHelpText: "Write a little about the workshop.  Why should a customer do this workshop?  What will it help them solve? "
            helpText:
                ```html
                Example: Developers today heavily rely on the most commonly used Cloud Native Computing Foundation  (CNCF) technologies to develop cloud native applications that can be easily deployed as microservices. Popular programming models used with these technologies are React JS and Java. Developers heavily leverage existing libraries such as those from Helidon technologies to substantially cut down development to production time and operate in CI/CD cycles.
                
                This workshop uses the Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) services including the Oracle Autonomous Transaction Processing (ATP) database, the Oracle Container Registry (OCR), the Oracle Kubernetes Engine (OKE), the Helidon microservice framework, and the API Gateway to build and deploy a Cloud-Native Application (My ToDo List) using the most commonly used Cloud Native Computing Frameworks and programming models (React JS and Java microservice).
                
                By hosting the entire Cloud Native application on the Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, a simple browser is all that is needed to access the application.
                ```
        }
    )

